thread.title: Unresponsive child who was hospitalized in Mass. died, DA says
thread.title_full: Unresponsive child who was hospitalized in Mass. died, DA says

author: Alvin Buyinza | abuyinza@masslive.com
title: Unresponsive child who was hospitalized in Mass. died, DA says
text:
A child who was hospitalized Thursday afternoon after they were found unresponsive has died, officials said.
The child had no signs of trauma, according to James Borghesani, a spokesperson for the Suffolk County District Attorney’s Office. They died around 3 p.m.
Authorities did not state the child’s age, name or gender.
Boston police said they went to 230 Bowdoin St. — the address of the Bowdoin Street Health Center in Dorchester — after they got a report about an unresponsive child around 2:28 p.m.
Homicide detectives responded to the incident in Dorchester Thursday afternoon, police said. However, their response was standard operating procedure.
